div.div: Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he cant rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bells trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and its up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeons dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)

When his father remarries, Yuta Asamura winds up sharing a roof with his new stepsister, Saki Ayase, the hottest girl in his grade. Carrying the scars of their parents troubled divorces, they vow to maintain a respectful distance. But what starts as cautious camaraderie blossoms into something deeper from shared experiences. Is it admiration, familial love, or something more? (Source: Crunchyroll)
Aoi wants to go to the same school as her childhood friend Yuuna so she transfers to Vlad Academy, but everyone except Aoi is actually a vampire!? Note: Includes 2 extra chapters.
Comedy, Drama, Romance, Slice of Life

When Ayumi learns that her senior Yuuki is heading to Minami High School, a fairly difficult institution to enroll in, she believes her current results are insufficient to pass the entrance exam. Despite this, he gives her a word of encouragement and promises to tutor her if she succeeds.
One year passes, and Yuuki finds Ayumi to be one of the new first-year students enrolling at his school. However, he also quickly realizes that his junior has become extremely flirtatious toward him! Now fulfilling his promise, the two experience many events togetherwhether they be funny, embarrassing, or even romantic.
